![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1d4469ea-03f5-4144-a542-cdcb318434ce/20240405_125006.jpg?format=original)

Professional wrestling fans were treated to a dream matchup when CMLL (Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre) officially announced a showdown between Bryan Danielson and Blue Panther, set to take place on a momentous night of wrestling action.

What makes this matchup particularly special is the stipulation CMLL has just attached to the bout: it will now be a one-fall submission only match, adding an extra layer of intensity and anticipation to the already highly anticipated encounter.

For Bryan Danielson, formerly known as Daniel Bryan during his tenure with WWE, the opportunity to face off against Blue Panther represents a culmination of a long-held dream. Throughout his illustrious career, Danielson has expressed admiration for Blue Panther, a Mexican wrestling legend known for his technical prowess and mastery of the submission style.

The prospect of stepping into the ring with Blue Panther is a testament to Danielson's respect for the traditions and history of professional wrestling. Blue Panther's influence on the sport cannot be overstated, and for Danielson, the opportunity to test his skills against such a revered figure is a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity.

The announcement of the one-fall submission only stipulation adds an intriguing twist to the matchup, as both competitors will be forced to rely on their grappling and submission skills to secure victory. With Danielson known for his technical proficiency and Blue Panther revered for his mastery of submission holds, fans can expect a clinic in mat wrestling when these two legends collide.

As the wrestling world eagerly anticipates tonight's showdown between Bryan Danielson and Blue Panther, the stage is set for a memorable and historic encounter. Whether it's Danielson's admiration for Blue Panther or the allure of the submission-only stipulation, there's no denying that this matchup has captured the imagination of wrestling fans worldwide.

In a sport defined by its rich history and larger-than-life personalities, moments like this serve as a reminder of the enduring magic of professional wrestling. As Danielson and Blue Panther prepare to write the next chapter in their respective legacies, fans can only sit back and marvel at the spectacle unfolding before them.